    "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n<!-- Every PR should have a corresponding issue that describes and motivates the work done in the PR -->\r\ncloses https://github.com/NVIDIA/cccl/issues/6865\r\n\r\n<!-- Provide a standalone description of changes in this PR. -->\r\nThe current implementation uses single block to reduce segments. This creates a performance bottleneck when segments are very large. \r\nThis PR implements two-phase segmented reduction where each segment is processed by multiple blocks, by dividing the single large segment into mulitple fixed size chunks and assigning each chunk to a block. \r\n\r\n<!-- Note: The pull request title will be included in the CHANGELOG. -->\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n<!-- TODO: - [ ] I am familiar with the [Contributing Guidelines](). -->\r\n- [x] New or existing tests cover these changes.\r\n- [x] The documentation is up to date with these changes.\r\n",
